Privacy-Preserving Data Exchange L1
Overview

Privacy-Preserving Data Exchange L1 is a blockchain network designed to enable secure data sharing without exposing sensitive information. The platform leverages cryptographic verification and zero-knowledge techniques to allow organizations to exchange data while preserving privacy.

Features

Zero-knowledge data verification

Secure encrypted data exchange

Permissioned data access control

On-chain auditability

Developer APIs for data marketplaces

Architecture
Privacy Layer

Implements cryptographic proofs to validate data without revealing the underlying content.

Access Control Engine

Manages permissions and identity-based access to datasets.

Data Registry

Stores metadata, ownership, and verification hashes on-chain.

Integration APIs

Provides SDKs and APIs for enterprise systems and data platforms.

Use Cases

Secure enterprise data sharing

Healthcare research collaboration

AI training data marketplaces

Financial analytics data exchange
